<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1941-11-10T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1941-11-10T00:00:00-05:00" n="543" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d543">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">740.0011 European War 1939/16685</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">Memorandum of Conversation, by the Secretary of
                                State</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1941-11-10">November 10, 1941</date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>The French Ambassador called on the President at the former’s request and
                            I was present on the invitation of President Roosevelt. The Ambassador
                            complained again about the British action at Djibouti. He, of course,
                            understands the grounds on which the British action was based, but he
                            was careful not to mention that phase of the matter. Very little was
                            said in reply to him in this regard.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>C[<hi rend="smallcaps">ordell</hi>] H[<hi rend="smallcaps">ull</hi>]</signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>